1999-01-31  John Harper  <john@dcs.warwick.ac.uk>

	* jadeclient.c: new option `-w' prevents waiting for server if
	it's not running. Detect `-?' option before waiting for server.
	If a socket exists but we can't connect to it, delete it then
	try again

1998-12-02  John Harper  <john@dcs.warwick.ac.uk>

	* server-dl.c (cmd_server_open): if the socket already exists,
	test whether it can be connected to; if not, it's deleted and
	re-opened
	* server-dl.c, jadeclient.c: format of socket file name is now
	.jade-HOST where HOST is the fully-qualified host name

